Package: alternativechillfunctions
Type: Package
Title: Functions to compute chill metrics
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2019-03-26
Author: Eduardo Fernández
Maintainer: Eduardo Fernández <efernand@uni-bonn.de>
Description: Develop some functions for estimating alternative chilling metrics for deciduous fruit trees. The package contains functions to use the models alternatives to the "Dynamic Model", "Chilling Hours Model" and "Utah Model", which are included in the chillR package (Luedeling 2018). These can also by used as input models for chillR functions. Additionally, this package contains a function to handle easily weather data from Chile, as well as a function to estimate metrics related to frost events.
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
Imports: chillR, sp
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
